{"cursor":"38022","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox scientist\n| name = Grigori Perelman image = Perelman, Grigori (1966).jpg image_size =\n| 300px caption = Grigori Perelman in 1993 birth_name = Grigori Yakovlevich\n| Perelman birth_date = birth_place = Leningrad, Soviet Union\n|residence = Saint Petersburg, Russia |citizenship = Russia |nationality =\nRussian\n| field = Mathematics alma_mater = Leningrad State University doctoral_advisor =\n| Aleksandr Aleksandrov Yuri Burago doctoral_students = known_for =\n| Riemannian geometry Geometric topology Proof of the Poincare\n| Conjecture awards = Saint Petersburg Mathematical Society Prize (1991),\n| accepted EMS Prize (1996), declined Fields Medal (2006),\n| declined Millennium Prize (2010), declined footnotes =\n}} 'Grigori Yakovlevich Perelman' ( ; ; born 13 June 1966) is a Russian\nmathematician who has made landmark contributions to Riemannian geometry and\ngeometric topology.\n\nIn 1994, Perelman proved the soul conjecture. In 2003, he proved Thurston's\ngeometrization conjecture. This consequently solved in the affirmative the\nPoincarÃ© conjecture, posed in 1904, which before its solution was viewed as one\nof the most important and difficult open problems in topology.\n\nIn August 2006, Perelman was awarded the Fields Medal {{cite web\n | work = International Mathematical Union (IMU) - Prizes title = Fields Medals\n | 2006 url= http://www.mathunion.org/general/prizes/2006/ accessdate = 2006-04-\n | 30}} for \"his contributions to geometry and his revolutionary insights\n | into the analytical and geometric structure of the Ricci flow.\" Perelman\n | declined to accept the award or to appear at the congress, stating: \"I'm not\n | interested in money or fame, I don't want to be on display like an animal in\n | a zoo.\" [http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/8585407.stm Russian maths genius\n | Perelman urged to take $1m prize] bbc.co.uk, Wednesday, 24 March 2010.\n | On 22 December 2006, the journal [[Science (journal)|Science]] recognized\n | Perelman's proof of the PoincarÃ© conjecture as the scientific \"Breakthrough\n | of the Year\", the first such recognition in the area of\n | mathematics.\n\nOn 18 March 2010, it was announced that he had met the criteria to receive the\nfirst Clay Millennium Prize {{cite web\n | title = The PoincarÃ© Conjecture url=\n | http://www.claymath.org/poincare/index.html}} for resolution of the\n | PoincarÃ© conjecture. On 1 July 2010, he turned down the prize of one million\n | dollars, saying that he considers his contribution to proving the PoincarÃ©\n | conjecture to be no greater than that of Richard Hamilton, who introduced the\n | theory of Ricci flow with the aim of attacking the geometrization\n | conjecture.\n","linknr":656,"url":"Grigori_Perelman","recorded":1371235532,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Grigori_Perelman&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Grigori_Perelman&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:Perelman,_Grigori_(1966).jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/43/Perelman%2C_Grigori_%281966%29.jpg/300px-Perelman%2C_Grigori_%281966%29.jpg","/wiki/Saint_Petersburg","/wiki/Soviet_Union","/wiki/Saint_Petersburg","/wiki/Russia","/wiki